                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/18974: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-01-27">January 27,
                            1942</date>.<lb/>[Received January 27—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Landing American troops port in Northern Ireland was broadcast yesterday from
                    London 9 p.m., from Dublin 10:10 p.m. This morning’s Dublin papers display news
                    briefly stating several thousand American combat troops with artillery landed
                    yesterday. Thus far no editorial comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
